S 17 naslovi za najuspešnejšo ekipo tekmovanja v zgodovini velja Boston Celtics, v zadnjem letu pa so naslov osvojili košarkarji Clevelanda na čelu z LeBronom Jamesom(n)

programme.title: Spanish league: Eibar - Barcelona
programme.desc: Španska nogometna liga, bolj poznana pod vzdevkom La Liga, je najelitnejše nogometno tekmovanje v Španiji. Ustanovljena je bila leta 1929. V ligi nastopa 20 klubov, kjer vsako sezono nekdo postane prvak in izpade v špansko drugo ligo. Najuspešnejša kluba sta madridski Real in Barcelona. Skupaj sta ligo osvojila kar 55 krat. Zadnji naslov je romal v roke Barcelone(n)

programme.title: Live! VTB Liga: Khimki – Kalev
programme.desc: VTB United League je mednarodna profesionalna košarkarska liga. Ustanovljena je bila leta 2008. Njen cilj je pod eno streho združiti vse najboljše klube severne in vzhodne Evrope. V VTB ligi nastopa 16 najboljših klubov iz Rusije (10), Belorusije (1), Estonije (1), Latvije (1), Finske (1), Ceške (1) in Kazahstana (1). Najuspešnejši klub je moskovski CSKA, ki je ligo osvojil kar sedemkrat

programme.title: Live! Portugal liga: Benfica – Tondela
programme.desc: Nekoč Primeira Liga, danes Liga NOS je najelitnejše nogometno tekmovanje na Portugalskem. V njej vsako leto sodeluje 18 klubov, vendar le pet je takšnih, ki so jo od leta 1934 (datum ustanovitve) tudi osvojili. Kar 81 od skupnih 83 naslovov je osvojila t.i. velika trojica (Benfica, Sporting in Porto) preostala dva naslova pa sta romala v roke Belenensesa in Boaviste. Aktualni prvaki so nogometaši Benfice

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 15 through 11. Included: City College of New York winning the 1950 NIT and NCAA hoops titles; Elvis Presley concerts from 1972; Bill Clinton winning the presidential nomination in 1992; a four-point, game-winning play by the Knicks' Larry Johnson in the 1999 playoffs; and the retirement of Mark Messier's jersey in 2006. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 20 through 16. Included: Marilyn Monroe singing “Happy Birthday” to President Kennedy in 1962; Pete Stemkowski's game-winning goal in triple OT in a 1971 Rangers playoff game; a dunk by John Starks in 1993; a putback by Patrick Ewing in a 1994 playoff game; and a 2005 concert for the victims of Hurricane Katrina. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 25 through 21. Included: St. John's victory in the 1965 NIT title game over Villanova; an amazing Knicks comeback over the Bucks in a 1972 clash; an Elton John concert featuring John Lennon's last public performance in 1974; Mark Breland winning Golden Gloves titles five straight times from 1980-84; and Games 3, 4, and 5 of the 1994 NBA Finals between the Knicks and the Rockets. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 30 through 26. Included: Joe Louis vs. Joe Walcott in 1947; the Rangers' John Davidson in the 1979 playoffs against the Islanders; the 1985 “Sweater Game” between Georgetown and St. John's; Hulk Hogan and Mr. T vs. Roddy Piper and Paul Orndorff in WrestleMania I in 1985; and a Knicks 1994 playoff win over the Bulls. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 35 through 31. Included: Led Zeppelin playing the Garden in 1973; Connecticut winning the Big East hoops title game in 1996; Michael Jordan scoring 55 points against the Knicks in 1995; 19-year-old John McEnroe beating Arthur Ashe in 1979; and ceremonies before the Rangers' first home game after the attacks of Sept. 11, 2001. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 40 through 36. Included: Mike Richter winning the MVP award at the 1994 NHL All-Star Game; the 1983 Millrose Games; Patrick Ewing becoming the Knicks' leading scorer in 1993; Billy Joel selling out 12 shows in 2006; and Reggie Miller's postseason play against the Knicks in games from 1994 and 1995. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 45 through 41. Included: Eddie Giacomin returns to the Garden as a Red Wing in 1975; Roberto Duran vs. Davey Moore in 1983; Bernard King scores 60 in 1984; and the No Nukes Concert from 1979, featuring Bruce Springsteen and Jackson Browne. (cc)

programme.title: The 50 Greatest Moments at Madison Square Garden
programme.desc: Numbers 50 through 46. Included: a fight between Evander Holyfield and Lennox Lewis in 1999; a hat trick by Wayne Gretzky in 1997; the play of Syracuse hoopster Pearl Washington in 1984; the first Grateful Dead concert at the Garden in 1979. (cc)
